text:
Clermont Ave., at the S.E. corner of Willoughby Ave., showing Simpson Methodist Episcopal Church.
July 22, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

Willoughby Avenue, east from Clermont Avenue, showing a group of remaining brownstone houses in this former fashionable Fort Greene Park district. On the right is a portion of the Simpson Methodist Episcopal Church and in the background, on the corner of Clinton Avenue, is an old private mansion. View 2 shows a closeup of the mansion, which was erected after 1893.

P. L. Sperr

October 12, 1940
Views 1,2
